    "body": "Add functional test coverage for the error path in `CheckFeeRate()` when `calculateCombinedBumpFee()` returns `nullopt` because unconfirmed inputs span more than 500 mempool transactions (`CTxMemPool::GatherClusters` DoS limit).\r\n\r\nThe crash on this path was fixed in #34870; this PR adds the missing test requested in #34902.\r\n\r\nThe test builds eight independent 64-transaction clusters (512 total, above the 500 limit), keeps a wallet-owned RBF transaction that spends one output from each cluster out of the mempool, and asserts that `bumpfee` with an explicit `fee_rate` returns the expected wallet error instead of proceeding with an empty optional.\r\n\r\nCloses #34902.\r\n\r\n## Testing\r\n- [x] `./build/test/functional/wallet_bumpfee.py`\r\n- [x] Temporarily removed the early return in `CheckFeeRate()` and confirmed the test fails with `bad optional_access` instead of the expected error message",
